TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {12361=Most of these situations come down to a people problem: Somebody thinks everybody is watching cows, but nobody is doing it! In other cases, it is a cow problem because cows are not showing heats. The latter problem, no ovulation but showing heat, is rare, generally only taking place when cows have follicular cysts. For more details on ovarian cysts, see the January 10, 2012, issue on page 21.}
